parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deformation and loosening of the fuel tank can cause it to fall off the motorcycle while riding, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: The fuel tank spreads or deforms
lifts off the frame at the front
and may interfere with the handlebars or controls. The tank may also develop bubbles or blisters on the outside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deformation of the polycarbonate fuel tank can cause it to shift and teeter while the bike is in motion, posing a serious safety hazard, including the risk of fuel leaks, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: The fuel tank has sagged or spread
making the front of the tank loose
the tank no longer sits properly in the mounting points
the tank rests unsecured on the frame
the front grommets no longer make contact with the tank
the tank is spreading or bubbling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion of the fuel tank can cause it to come out of its intended position, potentially leading to fuel leaks, fires, or other safety hazards. This can also cause damage to surrounding components and affect the overall structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: The fuel tank is visibly expanded or bulging
the fuel tank is not in its intended position
fuel leaks or odors are present
unusual noises or vibrations are coming from the fuel tank area.
